The paper proposes a multi-class adversarial architecture for partial domain adaptation, which involves aligning the marginal and class-conditional distributions in the shared label space. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), or multimedia (cs.MM). Among these, machine learning and computer vision are the most likely sub-categories, as the paper focuses on developing a model for transferring knowledge between different datasets.
